From: Ghaf contributors <ghaf@tii.ae>
Subject: [PATCH] nvkms: allocate NISO display surfaces contiguous for DCE proxy

The host-owned DCE R5 fetches NISO surfaces (pushbuffer, notifier,
semaphores) by physical address. nvRmAllocSysmem allocates them
PHYSICALITY=_NONCONTIGUOUS, giving a scattered guest IOVA the R5 cannot
resolve, so the window channel stalls (nvidia-modeset: waiting for GPU
progress, NVC67E). Force NISO contiguous so they take the physical
1:1-carveout path (at->flags.physical) the scanout surface uses.
---
diff --git a/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-rm.c b/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-rm.c
index fc5fb48..e16f6ec 100644
--- a/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-rm.c
+++ b/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-rm.c
@@ -2411,6 +2411,20 @@ NvBool nvRmAllocSysmem(NVDevEvoPtr pDevEvo, NvU32 memoryHandle,
                           DRF_DEF(OS32, _ATTR, _PHYSICALITY, _NONCONTIGUOUS) |
                           DRF_DEF(OS32, _ATTR, _FORMAT, _PITCH);
 
+    /*
+     * DCE host-proxy: the host-owned DCE R5 fetches NISO display surfaces
+     * (pushbuffer, notifier, semaphores) from memory by physical address.
+     * Non-contiguous sysmem gives them a scattered IOVA the R5 cannot resolve,
+     * so the window channel never advances ("waiting for GPU progress"). Force
+     * NISO surfaces contiguous so they take the physical 1:1-carveout path
+     * (nv_alloc_contig_pages, forced at->flags.physical) the scanout surface
+     * already uses.
+     */
+    if (isoType == NVKMS_MEMORY_NISO) {
+        memAllocParams.attr = FLD_SET_DRF(OS32, _ATTR, _PHYSICALITY, _CONTIGUOUS,
+                                          memAllocParams.attr);
+    }
+
     if (pIOCoherencyModes->noncoherent) {
         // Model (3)
         // - allocate USWC system memory
